\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Circuit-level paired Wilcoxon, $n=6$ (mean over 4 seeds within each circuit). $^{\star }$: $p<0.05$. VSR-post outperforms both ChipDiffusion legalizers on both metrics; the comparison to classifier-guidance is significant on violations but \emph  {not} on HPWL ($p=0.25$), which we report transparently. The seed-level $n=24$ test (supplement Table~\ref {tab:wilcoxon-seed}) gives the same direction with smaller $p$-values, but treats seeds-within-a-circuit as paired bootstrap draws, not iid samples.}}{7}{table.caption.24}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:wilcoxon}{{3}{7}{Circuit-level paired Wilcoxon, $n=6$ (mean over 4 seeds within each circuit). $^{\star }$: $p<0.05$. VSR-post outperforms both ChipDiffusion legalizers on both metrics; the comparison to classifier-guidance is significant on violations but \emph {not} on HPWL ($p=0.25$), which we report transparently. The seed-level $n=24$ test (supplement Table~\ref {tab:wilcoxon-seed}) gives the same direction with smaller $p$-values, but treats seeds-within-a-circuit as paired bootstrap draws, not iid samples}{table.caption.24}{}}
